parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the rear sway bar can cause the vehicle to become unstable, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The rear sway bar is broken or hanging loose
the vehicle is unstable or difficult to handle
the vehicle makes a noise or vibrates while driving
the vehicle's rear suspension is compromised.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission to engage properly can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission does not engage properly
the vehicle stalls or loses power
the vehicle is difficult to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to stop the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake light turns on
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down.
